  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "The primary requirement to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting is to be a **shareholder of record** (own shares directly registered in your name) **or have a designated proxy from a shareholder of record**.\n\nHere's a breakdown of the key requirements and considerations:\n\n*   **Ownership of Berkshire Hathaway Stock:** You must own at least one share of either Class A (BRK.A) or Class B (BRK.B) stock.\n\n*   **Shareholder of Record or Proxy:**\n    *   **Shareholder of Record:** To be a *shareholder of record*, the shares must be directly registered in *your name* with Berkshire Hathaway's transfer agent (currently Computershare). This is typically how shares are held if you bought them directly from the company (which is almost never the case).\n    *   **Proxy:** The far more common way to attend is to obtain a *designated proxy* from a shareholder of record. Berkshire Hathaway sends out proxy materials each year to shareholders of record. These materials include an attendance ticket request form. A shareholder of record can designate the holder of Berkshire shares held by a broker as their proxy holder for the meeting and request an attendance ticket for them.\n\n*   **Attendance Ticket Request:** To obtain an attendance ticket, you (through the shareholder of record who provides the proxy) must request tickets using the official form included in the proxy materials. The deadline for requesting tickets is usually in late March or early April. Berkshire Hathaway states that requests are processed on a first-come, first-served basis, and that there is no guarantee that requests for tickets will be fulfilled. Therefore, it's best to request your tickets as soon as possible after receiving your proxy materials.\n\n*   **Identification:** You will likely need to show a photo ID to pick up your credentials at the meeting.\n\n**Important Considerations and Tips:**\n\n*   **Brokerage Accounts:** Most people hold their Berkshire Hathaway shares in brokerage accounts. These shares are held in the name of the brokerage firm (or its nominee) and the brokerage firm is listed on the shareholder list. You cannot attend simply by showing your brokerage statement. You *must* obtain the designated proxy from a shareholder of record as detailed above. Contacting your broker is the first step.\n*   **Requesting Tickets Through Your Broker:** Your broker usually provides instructions on how to request a proxy from Berkshire Hathaway for the number of shares held in your account. They may have a form you need to fill out or a process you need to follow. Follow their instructions carefully.\n*   **Deadline:** The deadline to request tickets is strictly enforced. Missing the deadline means you likely won't be able to attend.\n*   **Ticket Limits:** There's usually a limit on the number of tickets a shareholder of record can request.\n*   **Verify Information:** Double-check all information you provide when requesting tickets to avoid any errors.\n*   **Confirmation:** Save any confirmation or acknowledgement you receive after requesting tickets.\n*   **Beware of Scams:** Only obtain tickets through official channels. Be wary of anyone offering to sell or give away tickets outside of the proper process.\n*   **Read the Proxy Materials Carefully:** The proxy materials contain all the details you need to know about requesting tickets and attending the meeting.\n*   **The Process Changes Slightly Every Year:** Stay informed and updated with any changes in the guidelines for the specific year.\n*   **Hotel and Travel:** Book your hotel and travel arrangements well in advance, as Omaha hotels fill up quickly for the meeting weekend.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nTo attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, you need to:\n\n1.  Own at least one share of BRK.A or BRK.B stock.\n2.  Hold the shares directly in your name as a shareholder of record, or obtain a designated proxy from a shareholder of record.\n3.  Request attendance tickets using the form provided in the proxy materials by the stated deadline.\n\nBe sure to check the official Berkshire Hathaway website and consult the proxy materials for the most up-to-date information and specific instructions for the current year's meeting.\n",
